    <h1>In good hands</h1>
    <h2>Here are some ways to pick a re&#xAD;li&#xAD;able prop&#xAD;erty agent</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200926/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-26"><time>2020-09-26</time></a>
        - <span>PROPERTIES LANDED HOUSES FOR SALE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Siti Ro&#xAD;hani</span>
    </section>

    <p>Buy­ing or sell­ing a home can be stress­ful.</p>
    <p>Any­one who has gone through the process can at­test to hours of re­search and pa­per­work, as well as some­times-tense ne­go­ti­a­tions with sell­ers.</p>
    <p>A good prop­erty agent should re­duce this stress. Apart from do­ing the pa­per­work, a good agent should also dole out ad­vice should things go wrong.</p>
    <p>If you are sell­ing a prop­erty, your agent needs to mar­ket it ef­fec­tively and cre­atively, con­duct open houses and ne­go­ti­ate with in­ter­ested buy­ers.</p>
    <p>If you are look­ing to buy a home, he should search for a unit that meets your needs and help you get it at the best price.</p>
    <p>There are more than 28,000 reg­is­tered prop­erty agents in Sin­ga­pore, ac­cord­ing to fig­ures re­leased by the Coun­cil for Es­tate Agen­cies last Jan­uary.</p>
    <p>To find the ideal agent, heed th­ese dos and don’ts:</p>


